From: Pulse Audit <audit@pulse.local>
Subject: [PATCH] feat(ai): add minimal eval harness for classifier + prompts

Currently zero tests cover the AI layer. The classifier
(src/lib/ai/classifier.ts) is keyword-regex with known misfires
("hoeveel eiwit zit in kwark?" classifies as nutrition_log; "gisteren
3000 kcal" falls through to general_chat). System prompts are 4500
tokens and change without regression coverage.

This patch adds:
- scripts/eval-ai.ts — runs 30 test cases through the live classifier
  and Claude chat endpoint, writes a JSON report with pass/fail per case
- tests/fixtures/ai-eval/cases.json — 30 canonical inputs spread across
  message_type categories with expected outputs
- pnpm run eval:ai — script wired into package.json

Run `pnpm eval:ai` after every prompt edit. Fail in CI when pass rate
drops below 85%.

---
 package.json                                |   1 +
 scripts/eval-ai.ts                          | 145 ++++++++++++++++++++
 tests/fixtures/ai-eval/cases.json           | 120 ++++++++++++++++
 3 files changed, 266 insertions(+)
 create mode 100644 scripts/eval-ai.ts
 create mode 100644 tests/fixtures/ai-eval/cases.json

